{"PubTator3": [{"_id": "11389482|None", "id": "11389482", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Am J Hum Genet. 2001 Jul;69(1):204-8. doi: 10.1086/321270. Epub 2001 May 29.", "year": "2001", "article-id_pmc": "PMC1226035", "type": "title", "authors": "Sambuughin N, McWilliams S, de Bantel A, Sivakumar K, Nelson TE"}, "offset": 0, "text": "Single-amino-acid deletion in the RYR1 gene, associated with malignant hyperthermia susceptibility and unusual contraction phenotype.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "2", "infons": {"identifier": "6261", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "68069", "valid": true, "normalized": [6261], "database": "ncbi_gene", "normalized_id": 6261, "biotype": "gene", "name": "RYR1", "accession": "@GENE_RYR1"}, "text": "RYR1", "locations": [{"offset": 34, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008305", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008305"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008305", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Malignant Hyperthermia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Malignant_Hyperthermia"}, "text": "malignant hyperthermia", "locations": [{"offset": 61, "length": 22}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract"}, "offset": 134, "text": "Malignant hyperthermia (MH) is an anesthetic-drug-induced, life-threatening hypermetabolic syndrome caused by abnormal calcium regulation in skeletal muscle. Often inherited as an autosomal dominant trait, MH has linkage to 30 different mutations in the RYR1 gene, which encodes a calcium-release-channel protein found in the sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane in skeletal muscle. All published RYR1 mutations exclusively represent single-nucleotide changes. The present report documents, in exon 44 of RYR1 in two unrelated, MH-susceptible families, a 3-bp deletion that results in deletion of a conserved glutamic acid at position 2347. This is the first deletion, in RYR1, found to be associated with MH susceptibility. MH susceptibility was confirmed among some family members by in vitro diagnostic pharmacological contracture testing of biopsied skeletal muscle. Although a single-amino-acid deletion appears to be a subtle change in the protein, the deletion of Glu2347 from RYR1 produces an unusually large electrically evoked contraction tension in MH-positive individuals, suggesting that this deletion produces an alteration in skeletal-muscle calcium regulation, even in the absence of pharmacological agents.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "21", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008305", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008305"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008305", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Malignant Hyperthermia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Malignant_Hyperthermia"}, "text": "Malignant hyperthermia", "locations": [{"offset": 134, "length": 22}]}, {"id": "22", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008305", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D008305"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D008305", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Malignant Hyperthermia", "accession": "@DISEASE_Malignant_Hyperthermia"}, "text": "MH", "locations": [{"offset": 158, "length": 2}]}, {"id": "23", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:C565498", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalized": ["C565498"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "C565498", "biotype": "disease", "name": "Hypermetabolism due to Defect in Mitochondria", "accession": "@DISEASE_Hypermetabolism_due_to_Defect_in_Mitochondria"}, "text": "hypermetabolic syndrome", "locations": [{"offset": 210, "length": 23}]}, {"id": "24", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D002118", "type": "Chemical", "valid": true, "normalized": ["D002118"], "database": "ncbi_mesh", "normalized_id": "D002118", "biotype": "chemical", "name": "Calcium", "accession": "@CHEMICAL_Calcium"}, "text": "calcium", "locations": [{"offset": 253, "length": 7}]}, {"id": "25", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008305", "type": "Disease", "valid": true, "normalize